# Template Conventions

## Naming

| Type | Pattern | Example |
|------|---------|---------|
| List page | `<resource>_list.html` | `appointment_list.html` |
| Detail page | `<resource>_detail.html` | `appointment_detail.html` |
| Create page | `create_<resource>.html` | `create_appointment.html` |
| Edit page | `edit_<resource>.html` | `edit_appointment.html` |
| Partial/fragment | `_<name>.html` | `_appointment_row.html` |
| Base template | `_base_<type>.html` | `_base_list.html` |
| Subnav | `_subnav.html` | `_subnav.html` |

Partials always start with underscore `_`. They must never contain `<html>`, `<head>`, or `<body>` tags.

## Inheritance

```
core/templates/core/base.html          ← root layout (sidebar, nav, scripts)
  └── app/templates/app/list.html      ← full page extending base
        └── includes _list_content.html ← partial for HTMX swap target
```

### Full Page Template

```html
{% extends "core/base.html" %}
{% block title %}Page Title{% endblock %}
{% block content %}
<div class="p-6">
  {% include "app/_page_header.html" %}
  <div id="content-area">
    {% include "app/_list_content.html" %}
  </div>
</div>
{% endblock %}
```

### Partial Template (for HTMX)

```html
{# app/_list_content.html — no extends, no html/head/body #}
<div id="content-area">
  {% for item in page_obj %}
    {% include "app/_item_row.html" %}
  {% empty %}
    {% include "app/_empty_state.html" %}
  {% endfor %}
  {% include "app/_pagination.html" %}
</div>
```

## HTMX Swap Targets

Define clear `id` attributes on elements that HTMX will swap:

```html
<!-- Full page has the target -->
<div id="item-list">
  {% include "app/_list_content.html" %}
</div>

<!-- HTMX request targets this id -->
<button hx-get="{% url 'app:list' %}?page=2" hx-target="#item-list" hx-swap="innerHTML">
  Next Page
</button>
```

## Template Blocks

Standard blocks provided by `base.html`:

| Block | Purpose |
|-------|---------|
| `title` | Page title in `<title>` tag |
| `content` | Main page content area |
| `extra_css` | Additional CSS (use sparingly) |
| `extra_js` | Additional JS at bottom of body |

## Form Error Display

Use shared partials from `templates/partials/`:

```html
{% include "partials/form_errors.html" with form=form %}
{% include "partials/field_errors.html" with field=form.email %}
```

## Messages/Toasts

Django messages display via the base template. Add messages in views:

```python
messages.success(request, 'Record saved successfully.')
messages.error(request, 'Failed to save record.')
messages.warning(request, 'Some fields were skipped.')
```

For HTMX responses, use `htmx_add_toast()` from `core/htmx_utils.py`.
